A Book and a Chat with Kathi Macias<br/><br/>&lt;a href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2F2.bp.blogspot.com%2F_t631HKKe2Dw%2FS8ng2wkPopI%2FAAAAAAAABGo%2FG3zZDlX3LEs%2Fwww.00%2Fakathi1.jpg%26quot%3B%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bimg"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_t631HKKe2Dw/S8ng2wkPopI/AAAAAAAABGo/G3zZDlX3LEs/www.00/akathi1.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img</a> style=&quot;float:left; margin:0 10px 10px 0;cursor<img class="smiley" src="http://www.pan.net/smilies/tongue.gif" alt=":)" />ointer; cursor:hand;width: 200px; height: 300px;&quot; src=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2F2.bp.blogspot.com%2F_t631HKKe2Dw%2FS8ng2wkPopI%2FAAAAAAAABGo%2FG3zZDlX3LEs%2Fs320%2Fakathi1.jpg%26quot"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_t631HKKe2Dw/S8ng2wkPopI/AAAAAAAABGo/G3zZDlX3LEs/s320/akathi1.jpg&quot</a>; border=&quot;0&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;id=&quot;BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5461143254517916306&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;It was really good to have my special guest making a return visit on today's &quot;A Book and a Chat&quot;. &lt;strong&gt;Kathi Macias &lt;/strong&gt;proved a very popular guest upon her previous visit, and it was great to hear what this wonderful author has been up to since her last appearance on the show.
<br /><br />Kathi is a multi-award winning author of almost thirty books, ghost writing several others along the way. Also known as &quot;Easy Writer&quot; for her and her husband's love of riding their Harley, something which as we found out during the show, has been restricted with Kathi having five books coming out this year.
<br /><br />&lt;a href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2F4.bp.blogspot.com%2F_t631HKKe2Dw%2FS8nqbENArpI%2FAAAAAAAABGw%2FcB2C-yfpyqc%2Fwww.00%2Fakathi2.jpg%26quot%3B%26gt%3B%26lt%3Bimg"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_t631HKKe2Dw/S8nqbENArpI/AAAAAAAABGw/cB2C-yfpyqc/www.00/akathi2.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img</a> style=&quot;float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;cursor<img class="smiley" src="http://www.pan.net/smilies/tongue.gif" alt=":)" />ointer; cursor:hand;width: 200px; height: 300px;&quot; src=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2F4.bp.blogspot.com%2F_t631HKKe2Dw%2FS8nqbENArpI%2FAAAAAAAABGw%2FcB2C-yfpyqc%2Fs320%2Fakathi2.jpg%26quot"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_t631HKKe2Dw/S8nqbENArpI/AAAAAAAABGw/cB2C-yfpyqc/s320/akathi2.jpg&quot</a>; border=&quot;0&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;id=&quot;BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5461153773869117074&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;During the truly entertaining hour long show, Kathi shared with us all about her new &quot;&lt;strong&gt;Extreme Devotion Fiction Series&lt;/strong&gt;&quot; the first two books from the so far four book series being launched this month. The first two books are &quot;&lt;strong&gt;NO GREATER LOVE&lt;/strong&gt;&quot; based in South Africa, and &quot;&lt;strong&gt;MORE THAN CONQUERORS&lt;/strong&gt;&quot; based in Mexico. These are to be followed by &lt;strong&gt;RED INK &lt;/strong&gt;based in China (Oct 2010) and &lt;strong&gt;PEOPLE OF THE BOOK &lt;/strong&gt;based in Saudi Arabia (Early 2011). During the show Kathi shared with us all about what lead to this series of books being developed, moving her into international fiction along the way. We went through each book and how it had evolved and what knowledge Kathi had learnd and shared along the way to producing, what I am sure will be a hugely popular series of book for this talented writer.
<br /><br />Not only is Kathi producing this set of book for 2010, she has also co-authored with Susan Wales &quot;&lt;strong&gt;VALERIA'S CROSS&lt;/strong&gt;&quot; which comes out towards later this year. 
<br /><br />That not being  enough for this lady, we learned that Kathi will be sharing some of her secrets with a writers help podcast in June.
<br /><br />&lt;a href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fkathimacias.eventbrite.com%26quot%3B%26gt%3Bhttp%3A%2F%2Fkathimacias.eventbrite.com%26lt%3B%2Fa%26gt"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://kathimacias.eventbrite.com&quot;&gt;http://kathimacias.eventbrite.com&lt;/a&gt</a>;
